To find (A △ B) △ C, we first need to find the symmetric difference (△) between sets A and B, and then find the symmetric difference between the result and set C.

The symmetric difference between two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection.

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 8}
A ∩ B = {3, 5}
A △ B = {1, 2, 7, 8}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between (A △ B) and C:

(A △ B) △ C = ({1, 2, 7, 8} ∪ {3, 5, 7, 9}) - ({1, 2, 7, 8} ∩ {3, 5, 7, 9})

(A △ B) ∪ C = {1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 8, 9}
(A △ B) ∩ C = {7}
(A △ B) △ C = {1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 9}

So, (A △ B) △ C = {1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 9}.
